# public/_redirects
#
# Netlify reads this file at deploy time. Rules are processed top-to-bottom
# and the FIRST match wins, so order matters: the more specific (API)
# rule MUST come before the catch-all SPA rule, otherwise the catch-all
# swallows the request and we get a 404 / index.html in place of the
# function response.

# Same-origin proxy for the Kimchi LLM API. This is the rule the
# `netlify.toml` redirect was supposed to provide, but on this site the
# `public/_redirects` file is processed with higher priority at the CDN
# edge, so we declare it here to be safe.
/api/kimchi/*  /.netlify/functions/kimchi/:splat  200

# Single-page-app fallback. Any request that is not a real static asset
# resolves to index.html so client-side routes (e.g. /projects/:id) work.
/*  /index.html  200
